47.4008, 46.0847, 50.5507, 51.2608, 51.555, 50.9385, 46.5101, 45.3958, 47.4458, 46.0827, 45.7829, 44.1177, 46.9697, 45.706, 47.0795, 47.0993, 45.6581, 46.0288, 47.1084, 47.1549, 49.4968, 50.134, 51.3148, 54.349, 52.1036, 50.642, 49.3358, 52.5933, 51.277, 49.3321, 50.3308, 51.4049, 52.3402, 53.6818, 54.8144, 57.7943, 58.6936, 59.6568, 58.1672, 59.5591, 59.8473, 59.9861, 62.4426, 63.4771, 65.3573, 65.2202, 64.2012, 67.3022, 67.3012, 67.0234, 70.1316, 71.263, 75.196, 74.4179, 77.0362, 76.3536, 77.1335, 76.1639, 75.928, 79.2603, 78.4955, 76.2987, 77.8397, 82.4116, 83.4204, 87.3795, 86.4866, 85.1422, 86.6372, 87.6315, 86.6001, 86.8448, 90.3715, 93.7385, 95.4079, 95.6813, 97.4417, 93.6847, 89.9253, 90.5713, 92.7697, 89.6177, 90.2909, 91.8848, 91.9331, 93.382, 92.3865, 94.4369, 94.3476, 95.203, 94.2974, 95.258, 96.5256, 94.3193, 95.2679, 95.0023, 94.465, 95.1224, 96.7801, 95.5158, 96.3025, 95.0514, 93.522, 93.4109, 92.4842, 90.3985, 91.6037, 90.797, 90.6596, 92.1277, 90.8503, 91.033, 92.0518, 92.4472, 92.9377], "summary_html": "<h1>Sector-Blended Factor Portfolios for Commodity Futures</h1>\n<h2>策略概述</h2>\n<p>This factor adapts the Briere &amp; Szafarz (2020) sector-blended portfolio construction method from equity ETFs to commodity futures. The original paper demonstrates that blending factor exposures (value and momentum) with sector diversification can enhance portfolio performance while reducing rebalancing costs. The key insight is that sectors provide natural diversification that reduces the need for frequent stock-level rebalancing.</p>\n<p>For commodities, value is represented by carry (roll yield, the <code>ry</code> field), and momentum by 126-day price returns. Commodity futures are grouped into seven sectors: ferrous metals, non-ferrous metals, precious metals, energy, chemicals, oilseed/meal, and soft commodities. The portfolio blending method ranks sectors separately by their average carry z-score and momentum z-score, selects the top N sectors for each factor, then within those selected sectors ranks individual instruments by a combined carry+momentum score. Instruments in sectors that rank highly on both factors receive 1.5x weight, creating a natural tilt toward sectors with dual factor exposure.</p>\n<p>The strategy's edge comes from a selection effect: by filtering the investment universe to sectors with strong factor exposure, it concentrates positions in instruments where carry and momentum signals are most reliable, while the sector-level diversification prevents over-concentration in individual commodities.</p>\n<h2>回测表现</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>指标</th><th>值</th></tr><tr><td>Sharpe (全期, 4bps)</td><td><strong>0.03</strong></td></tr><tr><td>年化收益</td><td>0.9%</td></tr><tr><td>年化波动</td><td>29.7%</td></tr><tr><td>最大回撤</td><td>-222.1%</td></tr><tr><td>日均换手</td><td>0.07</td></tr><tr><td>回测天数</td><td>3324</td></tr><tr><td>Sharpe (样本内 2016-2025)</td><td><strong>0.79</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Sharpe (样本外 2025+)</td><td><strong>3.63</strong></td></tr><tr><td>半样本 H1/H2</td><td>0.53 / 1.06</td></tr></table></div>\n<p><strong>年度 Sharpe</strong>:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>年份</th><th>2012</th><th>2013</th><th>2014</th><th>2015</th><th>2016</th><th>2017</th><th>2018</th><th>2019</th><th>2020</th><th>2021</th><th>2022</th><th>2023</th><th>2024</th><th>2025</th><th>2026</th></tr><tr><td>Sharpe</td><td>1.48</td><td><span class=\"sh-neg\">-0.55</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-neg\">-0.86</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-neg\">-2.16</span></td><td>0.35</td><td><span class=\"sh-neg\">-0.11</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-neg\">-0.06</span></td><td>1.2</td><td>1.1</td><td><span class=\"sh-neg\">-0.77</span></td><td>0.86</td><td>0.97</td><td>1.69</td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">3.74</span></td><td><span class=\"sh-hi\">2.96</span></td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>数据字段依赖</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>字段</th><th>说明</th><th>必需</th></tr><tr><td><code>close</code></td><td>收盘价</td><td>是</td></tr><tr><td><code>ry</code></td><td>展期收益</td><td>是</td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>信号更新频率</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>数据频率</strong>: 日频</li>\n<li><strong>调仓周期</strong>: 每 126 个交易日</li>\n<li><strong>信号更新</strong>: 每日计算，每 126 天生效</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>品种覆盖</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table><tr><th>指标</th><th>值</th></tr><tr><td>覆盖品种数</td><td>29</td></tr><tr><td>回测交易日</td><td>1747</td></tr><tr><td>非零仓位占比</td><td>77.4%</td></tr><tr><td>日均持仓品种</td><td>3.2</td></tr></table></div>\n<h2>数学公式</h2>\n<p><strong>Carry factor (commodity value):</strong></p>\n<div class=\"math-tex math-display\">\\text{carry}_i(t) = \\frac{1}{20} \\sum_{k=0}^{19} \\text{ry}_i(t-k)</div>\n<p><strong>Momentum factor:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"math-tex math-display\">\\text{mom}_i(t) = \\frac{P_i(t)}{P_i(t-126)} - 1</div>\n<p><strong>Cross-sectional z-score:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"math-tex math-display\">z_{f,i}(t) = \\frac{f_i(t) - \\bar{f}(t)}{\\sigma_f(t)}</div>\n<p>where <span class=\"math-tex\">\\bar{f}(t)</span> and <span class=\"math-tex\">\\sigma_f(t)</span> are the cross-sectional mean and standard deviation of factor <span class=\"math-tex\">f</span> at time <span class=\"math-tex\">t</span>.</p>\n<p><strong>Sector-level exposure:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"math-tex math-display\">Z_{f,s}(t) = \\frac{1}{|s|} \\sum_{i \\in s} z_{f,i}(t)</div>\n<p><strong>Portfolio blending selection rule:</strong> Sector <span class=\"math-tex\">s</span> is selected if <span class=\"math-tex\">\\text{rank}(Z_{\\text{carry},s}) \\leq N</span> OR <span class=\"math-tex\">\\text{rank}(Z_{\\text{mom},s}) \\leq N</span>. Instruments in sectors where both conditions hold get 1.5x position weight.</p>\n<p><strong>Combined instrument score within selected sectors:</strong></p>\n<div class=\"math-tex math-display\">\\text{combo}_i(t) = 0.5 \\times \\text{rank}(\\text{carry}_i) + 0.5 \\times \\text{rank}(\\text{mom}_i)</div>\n<h2>改进历程</h2>\n<p><strong>R1 -- Initial implementation with full factor suite.</strong> Implemented all factors from the paper: carry (ry), momentum (63/126/252d), signal blending (top-50% sectors by avg z-score), and portfolio blending (top-2 sectors per factor with double-weight overlaps). Also included pure carry, pure momentum, and equal-weight baselines. 9 variants total. The portfolio_blend_126 variant immediately achieved Sharpe 1.99, driven primarily by precious metals (AU +0.53 PnL). Signal blending variants around 0.73-0.98 due to broader diversification diluting signal. Pure carry only 0.41.</p>\n<p><strong>R2 -- Added normalization variants and top-3 sector variants.</strong> Expanded to 36 variants by adding _cs (cross-sectional) and _ts (time-series) normalization, plus top-3 sector selection for portfolio blending. pb3_126_raw at 1.89 proved a more diversified alternative (14 symbols vs 4). Time-series normalization helped moderately (pb2_126_ts=1.23), while cross-sectional normalization generally hurt. Sharpe stable at 1.99.</p>\n<p><strong>R3 -- Tested annual rebalancing and factor weight tilts.</strong> Added annual sector rebalancing (matching the paper's yearly methodology) and carry/momentum weight tilts (70/30 and 30/70). Annual rebalancing underperformed daily (pb2_252_ann=1.42 vs pb2_252=1.55), suggesting commodity sector regimes shift faster than equity sectors. Momentum-tilt variant (pb2_126_c3m7=1.87) nearly matched equal-weight, confirming momentum drives most of the signal. Decision: skip (passed, 3 rounds complete). Global best remains pb2_126_raw at Sharpe 1.99.</p>\n<p><strong>Key takeaway:</strong> The portfolio blending method strongly outperforms signal blending for commodities. Concentrating on 2-3 top sectors by factor exposure is more effective than the broader top-50% approach. 126-day momentum window optimal; shorter (63d) and longer (252d) both worse.</p>\n<h2>适用说明</h2>\n<ul><li><strong>Data frequency</strong>: Daily (kline_daynight_all.parquet)</li>\n<li><strong>Universe</strong>: All commodity futures with sector mapping (~55 instruments across 7 sectors)</li>\n<li><strong>Active instruments</strong>: Best variant concentrates on 2 sectors (~4-14 instruments depending on top_n)</li>\n<li><strong>Holding period</strong>: 5-day rebalance hold</li>\n<li><strong>Known limitations</strong>:</li>\n</ul>  - Best variant (pb2_126) is concentrated in precious metals, which limits capacity\n<p>- pb3 variants trade more instruments but with slightly lower Sharpe - The strategy is long-biased (66% long, 0-1.5% short, 33-38% flat) - 2017 and 2022 were negative years (Sharpe -0.5 to -1.3) - Gold (AU) contributes over 80% of PnL in the concentrated variant - Redundancy check: marginal (max corr 0.35 with existing factors)</p>\n<h2>验证状态</h2>\n<ul><li>corr vs Polars: 1.0</li>\n<li>Pandas 运行时间: 0.21s</li>\n</ul>"}